import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='delay', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('How does distance affect flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance_range'] = data['distance_range'].astype('category')
    chart = sns.countplot(x='distance_range', data=data)
    chart.set_title('What is the most common distance range for flights?')
    chart.set_xlabel('Distance Range')
    chart.set_ylabel('Count')
    for p in chart.patches:
        chart.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
